    legs
    Type: array 1…

    Ordered array of the different legs of this trip. Each leg can be of different type, defined in leg_mode with the same values as the query param mode.

        Simple leg, used for walk for personal_bike legs
            directions
            Type: array object[]

            Directions are only available if should_include_directions is set to true. They give precise information on the steps to follow for this leg.

            each object is a step, containing an instruction and some data about it.
                angle
                Type: numberFormat: double

                the angle to continue to the next instruction in degrees.
                duration
                Type: numberFormat: double

                the step duration in seconds
                entrance
                Type: object

                Details about the entrance when entering a transit station (optional).
                    raw_stop_id
                    Type: string

                    The GTFS stop_id of the entrance.
                    stop_code
                    Type: string

                    The GTFS stop_code of the entrance.
                    stop_name
                    Type: string

                    The name of the entrance.
                exit
                Type: object

                Details about the exit when leaving a transit station (optional).
                    raw_stop_id
                    Type: string

                    The GTFS stop_id of the exit.
                    stop_code
                    Type: string

                    The GTFS stop_code of the exit.
                    stop_name
                    Type: string

                    The name of the exit.
                instruction
                Type: string

                the detailed instruction to be displayed to the user.
                length
                Type: numberFormat: double

                the step length in meters
                pathway_mode
                Type: string

                The GTFS pathway mode for this step (e.g. WALKWAY, STAIRS, ESCALATOR, ELEVATOR, FARE_GATE, EXIT_GATE, MOVING_SIDEWALK). Only present when should_include_pathways is true and the step is part of a station pathway.
                polyline
                Type: string

                Shape of the step provided in the encoded polyline format.
                way_name
                Type: string

                the name of the way we are currently on.
